<subSubSection box="[1171,1828,533,600]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1170,1829,533,615]" box="[1171,1828,533,600]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">(BEAKED WHALES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="326" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1262,2142,681,908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• Medium-sized whales with spindle-shaped bodies and dorsal fins set two-thirds of the way along the body; adult males of most species have a single pair of tusks for male-male combat, and mostjuveniles and females functionally toothless.</paragraph>
<caption box="[1262,1506,875,908]" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="326" targetBox="[1396,2113,919,1106]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1262,2142,681,908]" box="[1262,1506,875,908]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• 400-1200 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption box="[1258,2034,1114,1147]" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="326" targetBox="[252,1200,684,1308]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph box="[1258,2034,1114,1147]" lastBlockId="0.[1297,2121,1114,1265]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• Cosmopolitan, inhabiting all the world’s oceans.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph box="[1257,2121,1153,1186]" lastBlockId="0.[1297,2121,1114,1265]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• Deep oceanic waters from the ice edges to the tropics.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1258,1734,1187,1225]" lastBlockId="0.[1297,2121,1114,1265]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• 6 genera, 22 species, 22 taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1257,2030,1236,1265]" lastBlockId="0.[1297,2121,1114,1265]" pageId="0" pageNumber="326">• No species threatened; none Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
